race.comment: This is tricky. UBER IN (1) did about what was expected here on debut and then spiked her figures when narrowly beaten this trip at Kembla Grange. She rode the speed in that and can skip across and do the same here. She will be further improved, and the Litt yard has a sharp record at this venue. ALL KIRKED UP (6) debuts for the smart Archibald yard and got to within 2L in her latest Randwick trial. Maps for the run of the race, and Alysha is a key jockey engagement. The betting will be key. COOL AS POPEYE (9) resumes for Pat Murphy and has trialled well at Goulburn. Had been cruelled by slow starts in her brief first preparation, but Louise Day has been with her all along, and we're likely to see improved gate manners. She will be naturally improved and looks ready to go. CAMILLA (7) is in a leading Sydney stable and is going well enough to win a race of this calibre. She was better at Orange last time and can build on that.
